3 Creating an account - 2 Log an ascent

<p>There are a few reasons why you might want to log your ascents:</p>

<ul>
 <li>Keep a record of the routes you've done and want to do.</li>
 <li>Allow friends to keep up with what you've been climbing (via RSS and <a href="/article/FacebookPublishing">Facebook publishing</a></li>
 <li>Help the <a href="/article/CragGuru">Crag Guru</a> learn about your climbing ability and style so it can recommend more routes for you to try</li>
 <li>Contribute to community-generated information and statistics like popularity, quality, seasonality, style and keywords.</li>
</ul>

<p>Here's how you do it.</p>

<h2>Adding a tick</h2>

<iframe title="YouTube video player" class="youtube-player" type="text/html" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/G2E5vgpS1d4?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowFullScreen></iframe>

<p>From the route page:</p>

<ol>
 <li>Click 'Log an ascent'</li>
 <li>Complete the details of your ascent</li>
 <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>


<h2>Adding multiple ticks</h2>

<iframe title="YouTube video player" class="youtube-player" type="text/html" width="640" height="390" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/_CW968PAHA8?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowFullScreen></iframe>

<p>If you've done several routes on the one wall you can:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Check the boxes of the routes you've climbed</li>
  <li>Click 'Log ascent'</li>
  <li>Complete the details of your ascents</li>
  <li>Click 'Save'</li>
</ol>

